  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Influencing Local Development through Utilisation of data and gender mainstreaming</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Compile nationwide gender disaggregated data on representation in the various district assemblies in Ghana, analyse and publish
Disseminate reports among civil society, government officials and the citizen
Conduct gender audit of programmes, policies and funds in 3 targeted assemblies
Support the 3 targeted District Assemblies to develop and or update gender policies 
Old districts (Akwapim North &amp; South) provide mentorship and coaching to the new Okere District Assembly for effective take off
 Training workshops 
 Periodic review meetings
 Documenting best practices
 field visits by project team</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Evidenced based local decision making supported by data and progress information 
Gender mainstreamed in the agenda and developmental processes of the assembly
Peer reviewed mechanism established among assemblies for improved delivery of public goods and services</narrative>
  </description>
